1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,293
- [moaning]
- [both grunting]

2
00:00:03,169 --> 00:00:04,546
- [gunshot]
- [screaming]

3
00:00:04,629 --> 00:00:06,297
[tragic music]

4
00:00:06,381 --> 00:00:08,550
[Gabriel sobbing]

5
00:00:08,633 --> 00:00:10,135
- Sir!
- Are you okay?

6
00:00:10,218 --> 00:00:12,429
- Are you hurt?
- Sir, I'm okay.

7
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,472
- But, Gabriel…
- Gabriel?

8
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:15,724
He's the shooter, sir!

9
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:17,600
- [Marcus] <i>Where did he go?</i>
- [Kyle] <i>To the rooftop, sir.</i>

10
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:19,853
[reporter] <i>Currently, we can see</i>
<i>that Agent Marcus Reyes</i>

11
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:20,895
<i>of Task Force Alpha</i>

12
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:24,941
<i>is on the rooftop of the school building.</i>

13
00:00:25,942 --> 00:00:27,277
- [Gabriel] Ah!
- Gab!

14
00:00:28,028 --> 00:00:29,154
- [Gabriel] Help.
- [all screaming]

15
00:00:29,237 --> 00:00:30,572
[Gabriel] <i>Please don't let go of me, sir!</i>

16
00:00:30,655 --> 00:00:34,117
- [Gabriel] I can't hold on any longer!
- I won't let go, Gabriel.

17
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:36,327
[Ramli]
<i>Jalil, I have something to confess to you.</i>

18
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:38,747
[Fatima] <i>Isn't he one of the people</i>
<i>who attacked us?</i>

19
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:40,999
<i>And now you're protecting him?</i>

20
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:42,500
Even if they're our enemies,

21
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:44,919
<i>we still need to show mercy.</i>

22
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:48,131
[Jalil] <i>Victory isn't measured</i>
<i>by how many people we kill.</i>

23
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:52,802
It's also measured
by our ability to show mercy.

24
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,262
What are you looking for?

25
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:55,346
Is this what you're looking for?

26
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:57,265
[Teresa] You kept it?

27
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:59,726
[Marcus] <i>I feel like Gabriel's with me</i>
<i>whenever I hold this.</i>

28
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:01,519
What's the name of that nurse?

29
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,439
- Why?
- I just wanted to thank her.

30
00:01:04,522 --> 00:01:06,858
- Her name is Jamilah.
- Jamilah.

31
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:21,748
[theme music playing]

32
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:32,175
[vehicle honking]

33
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:34,511
Boss, I'll be over here.

34
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:37,555
- [thud]
- [Andre grunts]

35
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:41,059
Geez!

36
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:42,393
You again?

37
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:45,313
It seems like
we keep running into each other.

38
00:01:46,147 --> 00:01:52,153
[stirring music playing]

39
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:53,738
What would you like to order?

40
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:56,533
One serving of steamed rice and…

41
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,368
That looks good.

42
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:01,746
And an order of stew
with extra sauce, please.

43
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,206
Alright.

44
00:02:03,915 --> 00:02:05,917
[Ara] Rice and stew.

45
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,341
[Andre] Extra steamed rice?

46
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:16,261
Hey! Thief!

47
00:02:16,344 --> 00:02:17,971
- [thief] Give it to me!
- [Gracia] No!

48
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:19,931
- Back off!
- Thief! Help!

49
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:22,058
- [thief] Let go!
- [Andre] Hey!

50
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:23,059
- [blow lands]
- [thief grunts]

51
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:25,854
- [blows land]
- [both grunt]

52
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:27,522
[Ara] Get him, Andre!

53
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:28,731
[shouts]

54
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,233
[clapping]

55
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:33,862
Serves you right!
Big mistake coming here, thug!

56
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:39,325
Miss, your bag.

57
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:41,744
- [Ara] Oh…
- [stammering] Thank you.

58
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:43,496
Thanks.

59
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:48,126
Wait, aren't you
one of the TFA members who saved us

60
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:50,253
at S. Trinidad Hospital?

61
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:52,046
I'm Andre.

62
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:55,925
Gracia.

63
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,679
Are you stalking me?

64
00:02:59,762 --> 00:03:01,347
Am I stalking you?

65
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:03,516
Of course not. That's inappropriate.

66
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:08,438
Well, I wouldn't mind.

67
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,565
You wouldn't mind me stalking you?

68
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:12,191
Why?

69
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:16,237
So what brings you here?

70
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:17,655
Are you here for a check-up?

71
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,116
Uh, please state your age,

72
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:21,826
your height,

73
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,995
and…

74
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:25,663
your relationship status.

75
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:28,207
I'm not here for a check-up.

76
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:29,918
We just escorted Sir Marcus.

77
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:32,128
Oh, right.

78
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:33,546
Doctor Teresa's son.

79
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:35,465
Don't worry.

80
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:38,718
Our residents are the best here.

81
00:03:38,801 --> 00:03:40,762
He is in very good hands.

82
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:43,223
[Teresa] Nurse Gracia, IV on bed four!

83
00:03:43,306 --> 00:03:45,350
Okay, Doc! I'm on it!

84
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:48,353
I-I have to go. The ER's very busy.

85
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:49,312
Bye!

86
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:53,608
[stirring music continues]

87
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:56,319
Flirting while on the job?

88
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,363
- Come on. Let's wait in the car.
- [gentle music]

89
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:00,782
I saw that, lover boy.

90
00:04:00,865 --> 00:04:01,699
[Andre chuckles]

91
00:04:05,453 --> 00:04:06,621
Sweetie?

92
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:07,705
[Kyle] Yes?

93
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:09,290
You don't want to eat?

94
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,084
Do you not like the food?

95
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:13,044
What do you want?
I'll cook anything you want.

96
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:14,587
I'm fine, Ma.

97
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:16,631
How are you, Kyle?

98
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:21,261
I'm going to get you a counselor
or a psychiatrist, okay?

99
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:22,804
So you can get professional help.

100
00:04:24,722 --> 00:04:26,349
That's a good idea, son.

101
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:29,894
What you went through was very traumatic.

102
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:33,606
Ma, Pa,

103
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,359
I'm fine.

104
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:39,070
- [breathes] At first, I was scared.
- [gentle music]

105
00:04:39,153 --> 00:04:44,158
But then I realized you were coming.

106
00:04:46,577 --> 00:04:49,706
I knew… I was sure, Pa.

107
00:04:50,206 --> 00:04:53,459
You wouldn't let
anything bad happen to me.

108
00:04:53,543 --> 00:04:58,214
[poignant music playing]

109
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:01,926
Of course, my son.

110
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:05,972
I will always be there no matter what.

111
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:09,809
[poignant music continues]

112
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:11,019
[Suzy breathes]

113
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,773
I'm worried about Gab.

114
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:17,859
What's going to happen to him, Pa?

115
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:19,152
Is he going to jail?

116
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:20,987
Is he, sweetheart?

117
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:24,240
But Gab's a minor.

118
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:30,621
First, we'll assess his judgment.

119
00:05:31,205 --> 00:05:36,127
If it's proven
that he was not aware of his actions,

120
00:05:36,210 --> 00:05:38,379
or that he was provoked
into committing the act,

121
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:41,007
charges will not be pursued.

122
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:41,924
[Kyle breathes]

123
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:45,720
But he will still be sent
to Pagasa Home, son.

124
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:47,305
For rehabilitation.

125
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:49,599
He'll be able to recover there.

126
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:53,019
Pa, I know what Gab did is wrong.

127
00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:56,689
But he isn't a bad person.

128
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:58,983
He's an ordinary student, Dad.

129
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:02,445
He was hurting. He was depressed.

130
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:04,614
And the ones who bullied him,

131
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,408
they also bullied me.

132
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:08,993
So I understand him, Dad.

133
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:15,041
I'm proud of you, Kyle.

134
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:17,293
Even though you were scared,

135
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:19,712
you still helped your friend.

136
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:23,382
[Azuelo] And don't you worry.

137
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:25,218
We will handle this case carefully.

138
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:28,096
Task Force Alpha will find out

139
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:32,892
how an ordinary student like Gab
got hold of a weapon.

140
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,811
I promise you,

141
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:39,690
we will make this world
a safe place for you kids.

142
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:47,406
[hopeful music playing]

143
00:06:57,542 --> 00:07:04,173
[Jamilah] Nurse, has Roger
from room 506 been checked?

144
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:07,468
- [nurse] Mm-hmm.
- Have Doc sign this.

145
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:08,928
Okay. I got it.

146
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:12,557
Be right back.

147
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,267
[Jamilah breathes]

148
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:19,605
Thank you again, Jamilah.

149
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:22,775
No worries.

150
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,902
Good thing I found it.

151
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:27,738
I didn't know that toy
was so special to you.

152
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:29,991
Yes.

153
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:33,202
It was my brother's.

154
00:07:34,203 --> 00:07:35,079
His name is Gabriel.

155
00:07:35,163 --> 00:07:36,122
[Jamilah sighs]

156
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:37,331
- [Marcus sighs]
- Mm.

157
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:38,624
[gentle music]

158
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:39,792
Gabriel.

159
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:43,421
You really love your brother, don't you?

160
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,467
Yes.

161
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:50,052
So much.

162
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:54,974
Even though he was so annoying.

163
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:56,934
[chuckles softly]

164
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:00,229
What?

165
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,482
[inhales] Nothing.

166
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:05,151
I just remembered my brother.

167
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:08,321
I annoy him all the time too,

168
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:10,948
but I know he loves me a lot.

169
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:15,870
[sighs softly] You know…

170
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:20,333
Gabriel is very lucky
to have a brother like you

171
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:22,043
who loves him so much.

172
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:27,006
[pensive music playing]

173
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:28,841
Thank you again, Jamilah.

174
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:30,968
You're welcome.

175
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:35,264
[pensive music continues]

176
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:44,857
[gentle music]

177
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:47,902
[morose music playing]

178
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,278
[Manuel] <i>I know it hurts.</i>

179
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:54,367
Lives were lost.

180
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:58,579
But you can't let…

181
00:08:58,663 --> 00:09:03,084
- [Lara breathes]
- …what happened to your parents

182
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,169
happen again.

183
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:06,546
[Lara sniffles]

184
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:12,176
[morose music continues]

185
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,263
- [explosion]
- [shrieks]

186
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:17,014
- [explosion]
- [people clamoring]

187
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:19,100
[young Lara crying] Daddy!

188
00:09:19,183 --> 00:09:20,768
- [distant gunshots]
- [screaming]

189
00:09:20,851 --> 00:09:21,811
[young Lara] Mommy!

190
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:23,229
[young Lara crying]

191
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:29,986
[grim music playing]

192
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:34,115
Mommy!

193
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:36,993
Mommy!

194
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,036
Mommy! Daddy!

195
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,413
Mommy!

196
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:48,087
[grim music continues]

197
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:06,939
[Lara] <i>Am I doing the right thing?</i>

198
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:11,402
<i>Or am I becoming a monster</i>
<i>like Datu Rahman?</i>

199
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:18,159
[grim music continues]

200
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:30,838
[unsettling music playing]

201
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:31,964
[young Marcus] <i>Gabriel!</i>

202
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:33,883
Gabriel!

203
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:36,469
Where are you?

204
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,596
Gabriel!

205
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:40,306
[breathing heavily]

206
00:10:40,389 --> 00:10:41,599
Gabriel!

207
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:47,980
[unsettling music swells]

208
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:49,607
- [boat creaks]
- [loud explosion]

209
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,401
[people screaming]

210
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:54,070
- [young Marcus] Gabriel!
- [Gabriel] Marcus!

211
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:55,446
[young Marcus] Come on.

212
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:57,198
- [people clamoring]
- [young Marcus] <i>Hurry!</i>

213
00:10:57,281 --> 00:10:59,158
- [Gabriel crying]
- [young Marcus grunts]

214
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:05,456
[breathing heavily]

215
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:10,586
[unsettling music continues]

216
00:11:15,257 --> 00:11:16,634
[safety box thuds]

217
00:11:16,717 --> 00:11:18,344
[paper rustling]

218
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:21,472
M/V DOÑA EMILIA CASE CLOSED;
GAS LEAK CONFIRMED AS CAUSE

219
00:11:21,555 --> 00:11:23,641
[intriguing music playing]

220
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:26,227
M/V DOÑA EMILIA CASE CLOSED;
GAS LEAK CONFIRMED AS CAUSE

221
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:33,442
[intriguing music continues]

222
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:35,152
M/V DOÑA EMILIA CASE CLOSED;
GAS LEAK CONFIRMED AS CAUSE

223
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:36,904
M/V DOÑA EMILIA SETS SEA ON FIRE
DUE TO GAS LEAK!

224
00:11:44,578 --> 00:11:48,290
[Marcus] <i>The authorities</i>
<i>ruled it an accident.</i>

225
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,585
<i>But was it really just an accident?</i>

226
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:55,256
<i>Who are you?</i>

227
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:58,676
<i>Were you the one who caused the explosion?</i>

228
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:03,305
<i>Are you the reason my brother is gone?</i>

229
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:08,602
[tense music playing]

230
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:26,078
[music stops]

231
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:29,957
[pensive music playing]

232
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,041
Auntie…

233
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,668
I'm leaving for now.

234
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:35,004
- I'm going to bring my father back
- [Aminah sniffs]

235
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:37,214
and clear his name.

236
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:39,383
Once my mission is over,

237
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:42,678
I promise all of you
that I'll come back here right away.

238
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:46,557
Jalil, be careful.

239
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:47,641
[Aminah breathes]

240
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:51,270
Give our regards
to Jamilah and Datu Rahman

241
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:52,897
when you see them.

242
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:55,065
Thank you.

243
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,693
Be careful.

244
00:12:58,277 --> 00:12:59,612
Take care of them, okay?

245
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,367
Take care.

246
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,248
[all] See you again!

247
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:15,878
[Sitti] Wait!

248
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,838
Jalil, wait!

249
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:22,551
- Sitti?
- [Sitti gasping]

250
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:24,470
I'm coming with you. [gasps]

251
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:29,683
I want to see Jamilah already.

252
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:32,728
- Sitti, you can't come with me.
- [Sitti gasping]

253
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:33,729
- It's dangerous.
- [Sitti] No…

254
00:13:33,812 --> 00:13:36,315
No! I'm coming with you.

255
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:37,858
[sobs]

256
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:39,485
- [Aminah] Jalil…
- [Sitti sobs]

257
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:42,947
- She doesn't have parents anymore anyway.
- [Sitti sobs]

258
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:45,115
Maybe you can take her with you.

259
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:46,408
[Sitti cries, sobs]

260
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:50,746
[Aminah] She hasn't talked
about anyone but Jamilah.

261
00:13:50,829 --> 00:13:53,415
She's the only person
she's looking for now.

262
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:55,626
So please take her with you.

263
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:59,296
[gentle music playing]

264
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,507
[sniffles]

265
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:03,801
You want to come with me?

266
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,637
[sniffles, sobs]

267
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,555
Okay.

268
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:09,890
Alright, come with me.

269
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:12,643
- [Sitti sniffles]
- Jamilah misses you too.

270
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:17,481
- [crying, sobbing]
- [gentle music continues]

271
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:21,902
Let's go.

272
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,237
[sniffles]

273
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,280
[groans]

274
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:26,031
Take care of yourselves.

275
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:27,658
[sniffles]

276
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:35,916
[foreboding music playing]

277
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:49,346
[Aminah sobbing]

278
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:54,018
[sobbing continues]

279
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,899
[foreboding music continues]

280
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:04,403
[music intensifies]

281
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:20,711
[foreboding music continues]

282
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:31,722
[somber music]

283
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:34,391
The school shooting that just happened,

284
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:38,687
where the suspect was
a minor high school student,

285
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:43,442
is just one of the many acts of violence

286
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:47,821
resulting from the continued spread
of illegal firearms.

287
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:50,532
There are so many questions.

288
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:54,578
How can an ordinary high school student
have access to a gun?

289
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:56,872
When will this stop?

290
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,999
And who should be held accountable?

291
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:01,418
<i>How can we have peace of mind</i>

292
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:05,506
if we're not even sure
our children are safe at school?

293
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:10,177
I hope the government
and those in power are listening.

294
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:11,887
And they better act soon.

295
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:14,765
Because people are asking--

296
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:18,227
No, demanding accountability.

297
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:22,356
[stirring music playing]

298
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:31,407
I heard that Gab tested negative
in his discernment assessment.

299
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:34,702
That means he'll be taken
to a rehabilitation center

300
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:36,537
after receiving medical clearance.

301
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:39,581
I hope he gets the help he needs there.

302
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:41,125
[gun clicks]

303
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:43,252
What's happening these days
is really alarming.

304
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:44,962
Even children are getting caught up in it.

305
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:46,046
[Andre sighs]

306
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:49,591
Those criminals
don't even choose their victims.

307
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:51,218
[Eve] Exactly.

308
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:54,304
How could a high school student
have gotten access

309
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:56,223
to that kind of firearm?

310
00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:01,145
That's why we need to work even harder.

311
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:04,732
We have to find out
who is behind this crime.

312
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:07,234
So innocent people, especially children,

313
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:08,569
don't end up getting dragged into it.

314
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:13,365
[tense music playing]

315
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:14,950
[gun clicks]

316
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:18,454
[gun clacks]

317
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:23,959
[reporter] <i>A school shooting took place</i>
<i>at East Valley Montessori</i>

318
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:26,545
<i>and was immediately responded to</i>
<i>by Task Force Alpha,</i>

319
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:29,089
<i>led by Agent Marcus Reyes.</i>

320
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:31,341
<i>Authorities confirmed</i>

321
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:35,846
<i>that the suspect was</i>
<i>a sixteen-year-old student</i>

322
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:38,474
<i>- who used his own firearm.</i>
- [somber music]

323
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:40,684
<i>According to the initial report,</i>

324
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:45,689
<i>the student obtained the weapon</i>
<i>through a popular gaming app</i>

325
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,107
<i>called "Cubix."</i>

326
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:50,486
<i>Meanwhile, the public praised</i>

327
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:53,405
<i>the swift response of Task Force Alpha,</i>

328
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:57,201
<i>especially the heroism</i>
<i>of Agent Marcus Reyes,</i>

329
00:17:57,284 --> 00:18:01,330
<i>who subdued and rescued the minor suspect</i>

330
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,248
<i>before the situation</i>
<i>could escalate further.</i>

331
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,459
[phone buzzing]

332
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:09,546
[buzzing continues]

333
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:12,466
Jalil.

334
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,676
Is there a problem?

335
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:20,015
- [Jamilah] Hold on.
- [Omar] Hm?

336
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:26,188
Do you know the name of that student, Ma?

337
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:29,024
[Marcus breathes]

338
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:30,025
Gabriel.

339
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:31,527
[Teresa breathes]

340
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,614
Gabriel?

341
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:39,368
[pensive music playing]

342
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:41,787
[breathes deeply]

343
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:43,831
While I was saving him,

344
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,794
<i>it felt like I was saving my own brother.</i>

345
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:53,048
Our Gabriel.

346
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:56,260
[Teresa sobs]

347
00:18:58,262 --> 00:19:00,097
- [sobbing continues]
- [Marcus exhales deeply]

348
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:01,807
[pensive music continues]

349
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:07,187
[both sobbing]

350
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:08,313
[sighs]

351
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:10,524
Honestly, Ma, you know…

352
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:12,651
[Teresa sniffs]

353
00:19:12,734 --> 00:19:15,487
sometimes I feel so exhausted.

354
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:17,614
[sniffing continues]

355
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:20,200
It feels like the people
we're up against are too powerful.

356
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:22,828
[Teresa sobs]

357
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:24,913
But back then,

358
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,126
while I was holding his hand,

359
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,213
I realized I couldn't let go.

360
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:40,095
- I have to see this case through.
- [Teresa sobs]

361
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:43,182
[Marcus inhales deeply]

362
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,225
For kids like him.

363
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:46,768
[Marcus breathes]

364
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,731
For kids like Gabriel. [breathes]

365
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:56,778
[somber music playing]

366
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,113
[young Marcus] <i>Gabriel!</i>

367
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:00,699
Gabriel!

368
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:08,290
[tense music playing]

369
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:12,085
- [explosion]
- [young Marcus groans]

370
00:20:12,169 --> 00:20:15,464
[tense music continues]

371
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:17,216
[sniffles] What's wrong, son?

372
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:20,052
[exhales deeply]

373
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:22,387
Nothing.

374
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,892
I just remembered something.
[breathes slowly]

375
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:33,649
I'll tell you once I've confirmed it.

376
00:20:36,526 --> 00:20:40,614
[somber music playing]

377
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:46,536
[somber music continues]

378
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,621
[Lara breathes]

379
00:20:47,704 --> 00:20:48,705
Hello, madam.

380
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:50,707
[Lara sighs]

381
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:52,042
Felix, what is this?

382
00:20:52,125 --> 00:20:53,710
Are we really doing the right thing?

383
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:56,171
[breathes]
Why are children getting involved?

384
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,714
Why do they have to be dragged into this?

385
00:20:57,798 --> 00:20:59,132
Why do the kids have to be affected?

386
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:04,096
[Manuel]
I know you have feelings for Lara.

387
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:06,640
Take care of her.

388
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:09,893
Watch her closely.

389
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:12,771
I care about her,

390
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:18,277
that's why I don't want her getting hurt.

391
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:23,657
The moment she becomes an obstacle…

392
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:26,368
…to our plans--

393
00:21:27,786 --> 00:21:28,578
Lara.

394
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:30,122
Lara, calm down.

395
00:21:30,205 --> 00:21:31,623
Listen to me.

396
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:33,208
Don't you ever say that!

397
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:35,002
Do you know what could happen to you…

398
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:36,336
- What's wrong with you?!
- …if General hears you?!

399
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:37,671
- Listen to me!
- Let me go!

400
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:39,256
- [loud slap] Enough!
- [grunts]

401
00:21:40,507 --> 00:21:41,341
[Lara breathes]

402
00:21:41,425 --> 00:21:42,634
Lara…

403
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:44,511
I'm only trying to protect you.

404
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:47,973
Can you just listen to me for once?

405
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:49,975
I don't need your protection!

406
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,519
I will protect you
whether you like it or not.

407
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:54,980
I'm protecting you from yourself

408
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:59,109
because you have no right
to question General's orders!

409
00:21:59,192 --> 00:22:00,610
Are you hearing yourself?!

410
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,112
You sound crazy!

411
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:03,822
Dad is not God!

412
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:06,700
Lara.

413
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:08,660
I am not afraid of God,

414
00:22:09,244 --> 00:22:11,663
because God is kind.

415
00:22:12,622 --> 00:22:14,041
But General…

416
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:15,834
I am afraid of him.

417
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:19,504
So if you want to live,

418
00:22:21,214 --> 00:22:24,843
never let General hear your doubts.

419
00:22:24,926 --> 00:22:26,595
Do you understand?

420
00:22:26,678 --> 00:22:32,392
[tense music playing]

421
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:46,656
[tense music continues]

422
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:55,082
[music becomes more unsettling]

423
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:57,334
[music stops]

424
00:22:58,627 --> 00:23:01,088
[somber music playing]

425
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:02,255
[sighs deeply]

426
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:08,428
[exhales]

427
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:20,107
- Do you remember my instructions to you?
- [upbeat music]

428
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:22,567
Yes, Jalil-- Oops!

429
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:24,152
I'm not supposed to know you.

430
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:25,153
<i>Who are you?</i>

431
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:26,947
I can't do this alone.

432
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:29,407
<i>This mission succeeded</i>
<i>because of all of us.</i>

433
00:23:29,491 --> 00:23:31,827
I'm glad we're finally on the same side…

434
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:33,245
<i>…Agent Reyes.</i>

435
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:38,834
The public's trust in the police
is slowly coming back.

436
00:23:40,168 --> 00:23:41,419
This can't be!

437
00:23:42,003 --> 00:23:42,921
You two are a good match.

438
00:23:43,004 --> 00:23:45,048
That's impossible.

439
00:23:45,132 --> 00:23:47,592
I'm Muslim and he's Christian.

440
00:23:47,676 --> 00:23:48,385
How is that possible?

441
00:23:48,468 --> 00:23:50,428
So much chaos is happening here.

442
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:52,222
All the chaos caused

443
00:23:52,305 --> 00:23:55,600
by the spread of illegal weapons
was intentional.

444
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:57,352
They're working together.

445
00:23:57,435 --> 00:23:58,603
They're figuring things out.

446
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:00,647
It's still just a suspicion.

447
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:02,524
But what if they already find evidence?

448
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:04,651
What if they find out the truth?

449
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:06,570
Then I'll just kill them all.
